File: Andile Mgxitama of Black Land First (BLF). JOHANNESBURG - The Black First Land First has opened a case of corruption against President Cyril Ramaphosa at Hillbrow Police Station in Johannesburg. The party's leader, Andile Mngxitama has accused the President of misusing the R 500-billion COVID-19 relief fund. READ: WHO chief brands COVID-19 protection gear corruption 'murder Mngxitama also accused Ramaphosa of receiving funds from what he refers to as ‘white monopoly capital’ to become the country’s president.